\title{revisiting the fundamental self-indexing}
\taxon{example}
\author{carloangiuli}

\import{base-macros}
\import{frct-001X}


\p{Recall that the [fundamental self-indexing](frct-001X) #{\SelfIx{B}} of a category #{B} is a displayed category with #{\SelfIx{B}\Sub{x} = \Sl{B}{x}}. Recall that [#{\SelfIx{B}} is a cartesian fibration over #{B} if and only if #{B} has pullbacks](frct-001Y). However, #{\SelfIx{B}} is unconditionally a \em{cocartesian} fibration.}

\transclude{frct-002Y}
